QuestionText: If Debbie's unique identification number is the first letter of her first name followed by the first letter of her last name and then the number for which month she was born, what is Debbie's unique identification number if she was born in December?
The time in New York is 7 hours ahead of the time in Denver. If it is 9 AM in Denver, what time is it in New York?
What is the sum of the interior angles of a triangle?
A snail is at the bottom of a 20-foot well. Each day, it climbs up 3 feet, but at night, it slips back 2 feet. How many days will it take for the snail to reach the top of the well?
The length and breadth of a rectangle are in the ratio 3:2. If the area of the rectangle is 48 square units, what is the length of the rectangle?
What is the value of x in the equation 3x - 2 = 14?
There are 15 students in a class. 3 students speak English, 5 speak Spanish, and 7 speak French. How many students speak only one language?
A bakery sells 480 loaves of bread per day. If they make a profit of $0.10 per loaf, what is their daily profit?
A bus travels from point A to point B at an average speed of 40 km/h and returns from point B to point A at an average speed of 60 km/h. What is the average speed for the entire trip?
If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how many minutes will it take for 100 machines to make 100 widgets?
